						<div class="postbody">They're asking how <em>emulators</em> produce 60fps images with transparency, scaling, rotation, etc. so quickly on PC hardware without hardware acceleration, not how SNES games do it (with the SNES' hardware acceleration, of course).<br /><br />I've never written an emulator myself, so I'm afraid I could only guess.</div>

