				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Emulators don't use floating-point math, for one thing. (Neither does the compositor in the actual S-PPU.) And they use an API optimized for speed rather than one optimized for genericity and colorimetric accuracy. It's not getpixel()/putpixel(); it's get a reference to an array of integers representing a row of pixels and write to that array.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
