					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The SNES has a screen brightness register; that's what most games would probably used to darken the screen.<br /><br />Nevertheless, the idea is the same: the emulator precomputes the darkened palette and uses it to draw the screen rather than doing a floating point multiply on each pixel after-the-fact.</div>

					
