				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I am not extremely familiar with the hardware, but I'm pretty sure floating point is not slower on PCs than fixed point. It is slower in embedded systems without an FPU. FPUs has been incorporated in PCs since much earlier.</div><br />It's slower in a lot of ways, maybe not so much on a per-instruction basis anymore, but when the whole pipeline is involved it's still pretty significant.<br /><br />SIMD instructions can help a lot with floating point efficiency too, but that's a whole field in itself.</div>

